success.question_text: If there are 180 students in year 9, how many were present last Wednesday?
success.question_hint:
• Find the percentage of students that were present.
  • Write this percentage as a decimal and multiply it by the number of students in year 9.

stimulus_2.text: Last Wednesday, 15% of year 9 students were absent.

review_3.column_1_text:
15% of students were absent.

100% – 15% of students were present.

85% of students were present.

85% of 180 = 153.

153 students were present.

Tip

Think carefully when answering questions. In this example it might have been easier to find the number absent.

10% of 180 is 18 so 5% of 180 is 9.

This means that 18 + 9 = 27 students were absent, so 180 – 27 = 153 students were present.

success.question_hint:
• A prime number only has two factors.
  • Work out the number of factors of 37 and 39.

review_1.column_1_text:
Solution

37 has no factors other than 1 and 37.

37 is a prime number.

39 = 3 × 13

The factors of 39 are 1, 3, 13 and 39.

39 is not a prime number.

37 is prime but 39 is not.

Tip

A prime number has exactly two factors: one and itself.

review_3.column_1_text:

The number halfway between two other numbers is the average of those two numbers.

success.question_hint:
• Work backwards from Rosa’s answer of 216 by using the opposite operation.
  • Instead of multiplying by 6 you should divide 216 by 6, and then divide again.

stimulus_1.text: To find the answer to a question Rosa needed to divide by 6 but instead she multiplied by 6. Rosa’s answer was 216.

review_1.column_1_text:
Solution

After multiplying by 6 Rosa’s answer was 216.

Before multiplying by 6 it must have been 216 ÷ 6 = 36.

Now, 36 should have been divided by 6.

36 ÷ 6 = 6

Rosa’s answer should have been 6.

Tip

Don’t rush into answering a question. Take time to think.

success.question_hint:
• Product means to multiply, and sum means to add.
  • To find the amount that has exceeded you should subtract.

stimulus_1.text: By how much does the product of 5 and 8 exceed their sum?

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

Make sure you know the terms used for different operations. To find the sum, add. To find the difference, subtract. To find the product, multiply. To find the quotient, divide.

success.question_hint:
• You can compare decimals by making sure all the options are written with three decimal places.
  • You are now comparing 030, 270, 123 and 032.

review_1.column_1_text:
Solution

Express each of the options with 3 digits after the decimal point.

0.03 = 0.030

0.27 = 0.270

0.123 = 0.123

0.032 = 0.032

In order the numbers are 0.030, 0.032, 0.123, 0.270.

The smallest number is 0.03.

Tip

To compare decimals write them with the same number of digits after the decimal point. Zeroes can be added to the end of any decimal without changing its value.
